--- TASK SPEC (plan/12, as read) ---

# 12 — Server: chat history cap and `history_truncated`
**Status:** pending
**Dependencies:** 11
Objective: Bound multi-turn chat task_input per API_OVERVIEW pull task: default 50 user + 50 assistant turns (configurable); history_truncated true when drops occur.
In scope: CHAT_HISTORY_MAX_TURNS documented; pull payload construction only.
Out of scope: UI copy (task 25).
Acceptance: unit/integration test > N capped + flag true; ≤ N flag false.

--- IMPLEMENTATION DECISIONS ---

- Capping applied at **pull** in `build_task_input` path (not changing enqueue in `sessions.rs`), matching spec “Pull payload construction only”.
- Follow-up detection: JSON object contains `session_prompt` (first chat job uses only `prompt`).
- `CHAT_HISTORY_MAX_TURNS`: default 50; `0` disables capping (documented as not recommended for production).
- Each of `history` and `history_assistant` trimmed independently to last N entries; `history_truncated` true if either dropped.
- On every follow-up pull, `history_truncated` is set explicitly to true/false after cap logic (overwrites stored false from enqueue).

